{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Fair Trade Commission |nativename = 公正取引委員会 |nativename_a = |nativename_r = Kōsei Torihiki Iinkai |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = Go-shichi_no_kiri_crest.svg |seal_width = 100px |seal_caption = |picture = Koseitorihikiiinkai.jpg |picture_width = 220px |picture_caption = Office building of Japanese Fair Trade Commission |formed = {{start date|1949||}} |date1 = |date1_name = |date2 = |date2_name = |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = {{JPN}} |headquarters = 1-1-1 [[Kasumigaseki]], [[Chiyoda, Tokyo|Chiyoda-ku]], [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]] |employees = |budget = |chief1_name = Kazuyuki Sugimoto |chief1_position = Chairman |chief2_name = Takashi Yamamoto |chief2_position = Commissioner |chief3_name = Akiko Mimura |chief3_position = Commissioner |chief4_name = Reiko Aoki |chief4_position = Commissioner |chief5_name = Yoshiharu Ojima |chief5_position = Commissioner |parent_agency = [[Cabinet Office (Japan)|Cabinet Office]] |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = {{URL|http://www.jftc.go.jp/en/index.html}} {{en icon}} |footnotes = }}
The {{Nihongo|'''Japan Fair Trade Commission'''|公正取引委員会|Kōsei Torihiki Iinkai|JFTC}} is a commission of the [[Japanese government]] responsible for regulating [[Competition (economics)|economic competition]], as well as enforcement of the [[Antimonopoly Act (Japan)|Antimonopoly Act]]. Headed by a chairman, the commission is commonly known as {{Nihongo|''Kōtori''|公取}} or {{Nihongo|''Kōtorii''|公取委}}.
On July 13, 2004, the commission asked [[Microsoft]] to remove a clause which it thinks is hurting activities of Japanese companies getting licenses of [[Microsoft Windows]] from Microsoft.
