'''Jan Lidén''' (born 1949) is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] businessman and a former [[Chief Executive Officer]] of [[Swedbank]], one of Sweden's largest banks. He graduated with a degree in [[business administration]]. Lidén started his career at the bank in 1990, working his way up the hierarchy before finally becoming CEO in 2004.<ref>[http://www.mynewsdesk.com/se/pressroom/swedbank/pressrelease/view/4083 Swedbank: Jan Lidén ny VD i FöreningsSparbanken], press announcement, January 21, 2004 {{sv icon}}</ref> He retired from the position in 2009, and was succeeded by [[Michael N. J. Wolf]].<ref>[http://www.swedbank.se/sst/inf/out/infOutWww1/0,,2700_m49_657272,00.html Swedbank utser Michael Wolf till ny VD och koncernchef], press announcement 2008-11-05 {{sv icon}}</ref>

